  "prompt": "How do I prepare for OPSC exam?",
  "response": "To prepare for the OPSC (Odisha Public Service Commission) exam, follow these steps:\n\n1. Understand the Exam Pattern\n- Familiarize yourself with the exam structure\n- Know the syllabus in detail\n- Check previous years' question papers\n\n2. Study Materials\n- NCERT textbooks\n- Standard reference books\n- Current affairs magazines\n- Government publications\n- Online study resources\n\n3. Subject Coverage\n- General Knowledge\n- Current Affairs\n- Odisha History and Culture\n- Indian Polity\n- Economy\n- Science and Technology\n- Geography\n- Reasoning and Aptitude\n\n4. Preparation Strategy\n- Create a structured study plan\n- Set daily/weekly targets\n- Focus on weak areas\n- Practice mock tests\n- Time management\n- Regular revision\n\n5. Recommended Books\n- NCERT textbooks\n- Lucent's General Knowledge\n- Competition Success Review\n- Yojana and Kurukshetra magazines\n\n6. Additional Tips\n- Stay updated with current affairs\n- Practice previous years' question papers\n- Join online/offline coaching\n- Take regular mock tests\n- Work on communication skills\n- Develop writing skills\n\n7. Optional Subject Preparation\n- Choose optional subject wisely\n- Focus on in-depth study\n- Practice answer writing\n\nConsistent preparation and strategic approach are key to success.",
